article.headline: UC Davis 85, Cal St.-Fullerton 74
article.story: FULLERTON, Calif. -- Vince Oliver scored a season-high 27 points and Mark Payne added 20 points to lead UC Davis to an 85-74 victory over Cal State Fullerton on Thursday night. Joe Harden, a transfer from Notre Dame, added 14 points and a career-best 15 rebounds for the Aggies (7-10, 2-2 Big West), who won at Fullerton for the first time in school history. Josh Akognon and Jacques Streeter scored 20 points apiece for the Titans (8-9, 2-3), who shot 36.5 percent. Davis held a 60-42 lead with 10:26 to play before Fullerton closed to within 66-59 with 5:55 left. Streeter drove for a lay-in and made a 3-point shot in a 40-second span to narrow the deficit. But after Harden drove for a lay-in, Payne made a steal and scored on a follow 19 seconds later to extend the Aggies' lead to 70-59 with 5:17 remaining. Davis then made 13 of 15 free throws in the final 2:55. The Aggies shot 55.9 percent.
